subject: ANN: XP DAY in Washington, DC - September 24th (5 days left to register!)
msgSnippet: Diaspar Software, Digital Focus and ProjectSuccess would like to announce that we are co-hosting XP Day DC 2005, a 1-day eXtreme Programming conference to be
messageBody:
Diaspar Software, Digital Focus and ProjectSuccess would like to
announce that we are co-hosting XP Day DC 2005, a 1-day eXtreme
Programming conference to be held in the Greater Washington DC area
September 24th, 2005.

This is a great opportunity to access some of the world's top XP
experts and learn from them through one-on-one discussion, tutorials
and open space dialogue! Past speakers include Ron Jeffries
(XProgramming.com), Mike Cohn (Mountain Goat Software) and Robert
Martin (ObjectMentor). At the cost of $249 USD, this is a can't miss
event for all levels of XP practitioners, including critics :-). With
only 5 days left to register and space being limited to 100 attendees,
register quickly to avoid disappointment!

For registration or additional information, please visit
http://www.xpday.info or contact me directly at the email address
listed in the header of this message.

Hope to see you all there!

Niraj.
